  "story": "One of the most cherished Tamil Christmas carols, sung in churches and homes across Tamil Nadu during the Advent season. This traditional nativity hymn paints a vivid picture of the birth of Christ in Bethlehem and has been passed down through generations of Tamil Christian families. Children especially love its simple, memorable melody.",
  "lyrics": {
    "structure": [
      {
        "type": "chorus",
        "lines": [
          "பெத்லகேம் ஊரிலே",
          "தொழுவத்தில் பிறந்தார்",
          "உலக இரட்சகர்",
          "இயேசு கிறிஸ்து பிறந்தார்"
        ],
        "linesRomanized": [
          "Bethlakeem oorilae",
          "Thozhuvathil piRandhaar",
          "Ulaga iratcahagar",
          "Yaesu Kiristhu piRandhaar"
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 1,
        "lines": [
          "வானதூதர்கள் பாடினார்",
          "மேய்ப்பர்கள் ஓடி வந்தார்",
          "நட்சத்திரம் வழிகாட்ட",
          "ஞானிகளும் வந்தார்"
        ],
        "linesRomanized": [
          "Vaanadhootharkal paadinaar",
          "Maeipparkal odi vandhaar",
          "Natchaththiram vazhikaatta",
          "Gnaanigalum vandhaar"
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 2,
        "lines": [
          "ஏழ்மையில் பிறந்தார்",
          "மாட்டுத் தொழுவில் வந்தார்",
          "மனிதரை மீட்கவே",
          "தேவகுமாரன் வந்தார்"
        ],
        "linesRomanized": [
          "Ezhmaiyil piRandhaar",
          "Maattuth thozhuvil vandhaar",
          "Manitharai meetkavae",
          "Thaevakumaaran vandhaar"
        ]
      }
    ]
  },
